
MPI Exercise:

The matmult.f90 code performs a matrix multiply in a crude way,
using a driver process to send out tasks for worker processes.
See what you determine about this mpi method (amount of communications
costs, the most widely mpi functions used, etc.).

    You will build the matmult executable.
    You will run it without remora, to make sure all is working.
    You will "attach" remora and acquire some details about the execution.

*******************************************************************************

1.) 

    cd remora/mpi
 

2.) Build matmult

    make         #FYI: checkout the makefile, how it sets TACC site flags

3.) Run the execution without remora

    TACC:
            ibrun -np 8 matmult


5.) Now execute again, using a remora capture period of 1 second:


    TACC:
           remora  ibrun -np 8 matmult



*******************************************************************************

